
1. FEATURE: Context/Domain Filtering
Current State âœ…
You already have the foundation:
TaskContext type: work | family | personal
ContextPicker component working
Database column exists
Design doc started
What's Missing (for beta)
A. View Mode Switcher Add a prominent toggle in the header (next to Day/Week):

[All] [Family] [Work] [Personal]
B. Filtering Logic
All view: Shows everything (current behavior)
Family view: Shows only context='family' + context=null/undefined for safety
Work view: Shows only context='work'
Personal view: Shows only context='personal' + context=null/undefined
C. Smart Defaults
New tasks: Default to personal (safe - nothing leaks to family view unexpectedly)
Tasks assigned to family members: Auto-set to family
Calendar events: Default to family (since they're shared)
D. Projects inherit context Add context field to projects, tasks inherit from their project
My Recommendation
For beta launch, implement the minimum:
âœ… View mode toggle (All/Family/Work/Personal)
âœ… Filter tasks/events/routines by context
âœ… Default new tasks to personal
âœ… Auto-set assigned tasks to family
â¸ï¸ Skip project context inheritance for now (can add post-beta)
Why this matters for beta: Your vision mentions "Family is just a domain that happens to be shared" - this is the core differentiator. Users need to trust that their private stuff stays private.
2. VISION / BETA MESSAGING
Current Vision Issues
Your VISION.md is too technical and scope-confused. It reads like internal documentation, not user-facing messaging. Also, it says "V1" = minimal features but your current app is way beyond that.
Recommended Beta Messaging
Here's how I'd describe Symphony for beta users:
Symphony: Your Life, Organized The personal operating system that keeps work, family, and personal life in harmony. The Problem We Solve You capture tasks in 5 different apps. Calendar events here, work tasks there, family stuff somewhere else. When it's time to actually DO something, you're frantically searching for the context: "Where did I write those blinds measurements? What was the phone number? Which website?" How Symphony Works
Capture everything in one place - Tasks, events, notes, links, files. Quick add from anywhere.
See what matters, when it matters - Context-aware timeline shows only what's relevant right now, with everything attached.
Your domains, your rules - Keep work private, family shared, personal separate. One app, multiple contexts that don't bleed together.
Desktop planning, mobile execution - Plan your week on a big screen. Execute on mobile with all the context at your fingertips.
What Makes Symphony Different
Context-first: Not just a task list - every task carries its full context (notes, links, files, location)
Multi-domain: Work/family/personal separation built-in, not bolted on
Calendar-integrated: Google Calendar is the source of truth, Symphony adds the context layer
Execution-focused: Shows you exactly what you need, exactly when you need it
Current Beta Features
âœ… Tasks with rich context (notes, links, files, locations)
âœ… Google Calendar integration
âœ… Projects & contacts
âœ… Routines & recurring tasks
âœ… Family member assignment
âœ… Context filtering (work/family/personal views)
âœ… Mobile + desktop optimized
âœ… Notes & lists
âœ… Trip planning with packing templates
Who Is This For? Beta users should be people who:
Manage both personal and family responsibilities
Feel overwhelmed by scattered information
Want ONE system that handles all life domains
Value privacy (work stays separate from family screens)
Plan on desktop, execute on mobile
Beta Onboarding Flow
Welcome screen: "Symphony helps you organize work, family, and personal life - all in one place."
