That's the key insight. The word makes you question "Is this worthy of being called a project?" What about "Topic"? Examples:
Topic: "Blinds"
Topic: "Energy Grant"
Topic: "Meg follow-up"
Why it might work:
No implied scale ("big topic" or "small topic" both make sense)
Natural: "These tasks are all about the same topic"
Low commitment - topics are casual
No mental speed bump
Would "Add to topic" feel lighter than "Add to project"?
